# Agmsg Lanes

Use this when the project enables Agmsg.

Workspace rule source:

- `..\..\System\docs\agmsg.md`
- `..\..\System\docs\agent-roles.md`
- `..\..\System\docs\services.md`

## Lane Contract

- Agmsg carries short pointers, ACKs, status, and artifact paths.
- GitHub remains the official source of truth after publication.
- Do not put secrets, raw credentials, browser state, or long transcripts in
  Agmsg.
- Use `required_reply=answer` only when a human or lane session is expected to
  consume the inbox during the milestone.
- Reply mechanics are lane-specific. CursorAgent runs the explicit
  `agmsg-send.ps1` reply command in its prompt; `claude-ui-consult.ps1` and
  `grok-consult.ps1` post short replies after saving report artifacts.
- Grok live calls are opt-in. If Grok is rate-limited or the user has not
  explicitly allowed a live Grok call, keep Grok pointer-only and use
  Cursor/Claude-only smoke coverage.

## Smoke

From the Tools root:

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\System\scripts\agmsg-console.ps1 -Project .\Projects\<Project> -NoConsume
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\System\scripts\agmsg-trace.ps1 -CorrelationId <id>
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\System\scripts\agmsg-roundtrip-smoke.ps1 -Project .\Projects\<Project> -Lane cursor,claude
```

Record the result in the project issue or milestone report.
